# Example only -- copy to .env.local (gitignored, never committed) and adjust
# the value to match your actual local Vite dev server origin.
#
# SUPABASE_URL, SUPABASE_ANON_KEY, and SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY are injected
# automatically by the Supabase CLI for `supabase functions serve` and must
# NOT be set here (decisions.md #25).
#
# WORKER_INVITE_REDIRECT_URL must match the origin the Vite dev server is
# actually running on -- `bun run dev` / `vite` defaults to port 5173 unless
# started with an explicit --port. Do not use 127.0.0.1:3000 unless the app
# is actually running there; a mismatched origin sends invite links to a
# page that never loads. In production, set this to the real production app
# URL instead (as a remote Supabase secret, never in this file).
#
# Whatever value you set here must also be allow-listed in
# supabase/config.toml's [auth] additional_redirect_urls (or match site_url)
# -- otherwise GoTrue silently falls back to site_url with no path instead of
# erroring, which sends every invite/recovery link to a page that doesn't
# render the set-password form (the drift found during Phase 11C-2 local
# verification). localhost:5173 and 127.0.0.1:5173 (with and without
# /set-password) are already allow-listed there.
WORKER_INVITE_REDIRECT_URL=http://localhost:5173/set-password
